Package com.mewna.catnip.util

Class VoidHelper

java.lang.Object
com.mewna.catnip.util.VoidHelper
public final class VoidHelper
extends Object
A horrible, ugly, no-good, very-bad hack, but it's necessary. In the pagination classes (used for ex. batch message pagination), we have a situation where we compose observables in a chain, then terminate by returning an empty Observable<Void>. The problem with this is that we can't just shove a null into it, as that's illegal in Rx2 operators because reasons. Returning a Completable isn't an option either because it's really a Observable<T> | Observable<Void> return type, for reasons I'd rather not try and work out since I didn't write that code. To get around this issue, we do the horrible, awful hack of instantiating a Void and storing it for use in those cases.
Since:
3/8/20.

amy
